ZH: 这本小说歪曲了历史事实。
EN: This novel distorts historical facts.

ZH: 媒体应该避免歪曲新闻报道。
EN: The media should avoid distorting news reports.

ZH: 他经常歪曲别人的意思。
EN: He often distorts other people's intentions.

ZH: 这篇文章是对真相的歪曲。
EN: This article is a distortion of the truth.

ZH: 我不喜欢歪曲事实的人。
EN: I dislike people who distort the facts.

ZH: 他故意歪曲了我的观点。
EN: He deliberately distorted my point of view.

ZH: 这个政党经常歪曲他们的竞选承诺。
EN: This political party often distorts their campaign promises.

ZH: 她的评论充满了对事实的歪曲。
EN: Her comments are filled with distortions of the facts.

ZH: 不要歪曲我的话！
EN: Don't twist my words!

ZH: 这个广告歪曲了产品的效果。
EN: This advertisement distorts the effectiveness of the product.

ZH: 不要被谣言歪曲了判断。
EN: Don't let rumors distort your judgment.

ZH: 这个论点夸大和歪曲了事实。
EN: This argument exaggerates and distorts the facts.

ZH: 他的陈述有意歪曲了真相。
EN: His statement deliberately distorted the truth.

ZH: 这种报道明显是对事实的歪曲。
EN: This report is clearly a distortion of the facts.

ZH: 这个演员将历史人物歪曲成了喜剧角色。
EN: This actor distorts historical figures into comedy characters.

ZH: 学生们被误导和歪曲了历史事件。
EN: The students were misled and had distorted views on historical events.

